    "<h2 class=\"book-title\">Grammar - Level 8</h2>",
    "<h3>The Present Passive</h3>",
    "<h4>A. Look at these sentences:</h4>",
    "<p class=\"sentence\">* Japan produces cars.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence-notes\"><span class=\"left-7\">Subject<span> <span class=\"left-14\"> verb</span> <span class=\"left-14\">object</span></p>",
    "<p>This verb has an object. It is a transitive verb.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence\">* The Japanese came to the presentation at the car factory.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence-notes\"><span class=\"left-33\">Subject</span> <span class=\"left-32\">verb</span></p>",
    "<p>This verb does not have an object. It is an intransitive verb. Only <u>transitive verbs</u> can be made passive.</p>",
    "<h4>B. Look at these sentences:</h4>",
    "<p class=\"sentence\">* Japan produces cars.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence-notes\"> <span class=\"left-9\"> subject</span> <span class=\"left-12\">verb</span> <span class=\"left-20\">object</span></p>",
    "<p>Active verb. The sentence tells us <u>what the subject does</u>.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence\">* Cars are produced in Japan.</p>",
    "<p class=\"sentence-notes\"><span class=\"left-1\">Subject</span> <span class=\"left-1\">verb</span></p>",
    "<p>Passive verb. The sentence tells us <u>what happens to the subject</u>. The object of the active sentence becomes the subject of the passive sentence.</p>",
    "<h4>C. FORM:</h4>",
    "<p>The present passive is formed with the appropriate present form of the verb be and the past participle of the verb.</p>",
